Package: interpElections
Title: Spatial Interpolation of Electoral Data via Inverse Distance Weighting
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Rogerio", "Barbosa", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "rogerio.barbosa@iesp.uerj.br"),
    person("Lucas", "Gelape", role = "aut"))
Description: Interpolates voting counts and electoral demographics from
    polling locations into census tracts using inverse distance weighting
    with column-normalized weights and per-zone optimized decay parameters.
    Travel-time matrices are computed via the r5r routing engine.
    Optimization uses per-bracket stochastic gradient descent with
    log-barrier penalty on CPU or GPU via torch. Includes end-to-end
    helpers for Brazilian electoral data that auto-download census,
    electoral, and road network data.
